Dear Antonio, I prepare a bat file to install mod harbour.

md c:\Apache24
cd c:\Apache24
md c:\Apache24\htdocs
cd c:\Apache24\htdocs

mklink /h libharbour.dll c:\mod_harbour\windows\win64\libharbour.dll

cd..
cd c:\xampp\htdocs
mklink /j modharbour_samples c:\mod_harbour\samples
mklink /h libharbour.dll c:\mod_harbour\windows\win64\libharbour.dll

cd..
cd c:\xampp\apache\htdocs
mklink /h libharbour.dll c:\mod_harbour\windows\win64\libharbour.dll


cd..
cd c:\xampp\apache
mklink /h mod_harbour.so c:\mod_harbour\windows\win64\mod_harbour.so


cd..
cd  c:\xampp\apache\modules
mklink /h mod_harbour.so c:\mod_harbour\windows\win64\mod_harbour.so
but now I saw that git is installing

c:\xampp\apache/mod_harbour.so

should we delete these mod_harbour.so and create pointers or no pointers and let GIT do that?
